Constructor Detail

Simulation

public Simulation(Project project,
                  String machine_name,
                  Tape tape)
           throws SimulationException
Constructs a simulation. The simulation starts from the state named "start" in the specified machine.

Parameters:
project - The project to simulate.
machine_name - The name of the machine in the project to simulate.
tape - The input tape to simulate on.
Throws:
SimulationException - if the project doesn't have the machine or the machine does not have a start state or a submachine error occured.
Method Detail

getStatus

public SimulationStatus getStatus()
Gets the current status of the simulation.

Returns:
The status of the simulation. If ACCEPTED, the simulation has met an accepting state. If REJECTED, the simulation has met a state from which it could not continue from. Otherwise, it is still RUNNING.

getState

public State getState()
Gets the state the simulation is currently/was last.

Returns:
If the simulation status is REJECTED, the state from which the simulation could not continue. If the simulation status is ACCEPTED, the accepting state of the simulation. Otherwise the current state.

getMachine

public Machine getMachine()
Gets the machine the simulation is currently/was last.

Returns:
The machine getState() is in.

getHead

public Head getHead()
Gets the head of the simulation.

Returns:
The head that is used throughout the simulation.

getTape

public Tape getTape()
Gets the tape the simulation operates on.

Returns:
The tape that the simulation operates on.

step

public void step()
          throws SimulationException
If the simulation is still running, runs it one transition forward. After that, steps into and out of submachines such that next step starts again with a transition.

Throws:
SimulationException - on submachine errors.

run

public void run()
         throws SimulationException
Step the simulation until the status is no longer RUNNING. Note that if the simulation might not terminate.

Throws:
SimulationException - on submachine errors.
